## 🛠️ Security Lab Setup
### *Malware Analysis Environment*
To perform this assessment without risking the host machine, a hardened sandbox environment was utilized. This prevents "guest-to-host" escapes and ensures any malicious payloads are contained within a disposable instance.

* [cite_start]**Isolation:** The analysis was conducted in a virtualized workstation with no network connectivity to local production assets[cite: 1].
* [cite_start]**Peripheral Handling:** The suspicious USB was mounted as a pass-through device to the virtual environment, ensuring the host operating system's AutoPlay remained inactive[cite: 1].
* [cite_start]**Persistence:** All analysis was performed in a non-persistent session, where any changes or potential infections were discarded upon completion[cite: 1].

